<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-12T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="1303" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1303">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/7–1249: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-12T16:00:00+08:00">July 12,
                                    1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 12—7:11 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1487. [To Shanghai:] ReEmbtel 1486, July 12 to Department; repeated
                            Shanghai 829. Before your departure [from] Shanghai, suggest you
                            discreetly canvass few selected leaders American business, educational,
                            religious community to ascertain approximate number Americans who would
                            respond to plan for repatriation vessel. Information will probably be
                            useful if you plan follow up this proposal after your arrival
                            Washington.</p>
                        <p>Sent Shanghai 830; repeated Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>